sudo apt-get update - synchronisates information from repasitory with local cache
sudo apt full-upgrade - update system and all pockets and programs
sudo apt-get install "program name" - installs current program
sudo apt-get remove "program name" - deletes current program but saves configuration files
sudo apt-get purge "program name" - deletes current program with configuration files
sudo apt-get check
sudo apt-get autoclean - deletes old archive packets

df -h - information about disk storage
sudo passwd root - change root password
sudo -i - enter root and exit from all directories
su - enter root without exiting from current directory
uptime - It is used to find out how long the system is active (running)
mkdir - create directory
mkdir -p - create many directories as path
cat - read the file
cat /etc/os-release - information about linux os
cd /sbin - in 'sbin' directory are stored executable programs by root users
cd /bin - in 'bin' directory are stored executable programs by normal users
cd /etc - in 'etc' directory are stored configuration files and directories
cp - copy files
cp -r - copy directories
mv - move files
rm - remove files
rmdir - remove empty directory
rm -r - remove directory with his files
rm -r * - remove everything in directory
free -m - RAM parameters
touch filename{1..10} - creating 10 files with name 'filename'
file "file path" - shows file type
ls -l - shows all files with information about creating data and access
ls -a - same as ls -l + hidden files
ln -s "original file type" "link file path" - creating file shortcut(link)



filters

grep 'word in file' 'file name' - finiding line with this word in file
grep -i 'word in file' 'file name' - finiding all lines with this word in file  (անկախ նրանից թե բառը մեծատառ է թե փոքրատառ)
grep -i 'word in files' * - finding all lines with this word in all files in current directory  (անկախ նրանից թե բառը մեծատառ է թե փոքրատառ)
grep -iR 'word in files' * - finding all lines with this word in all files in current directory and shows this file locations (անկախ նրանից թե բառը մեծատառ է թե փոքրատառ)


redirecting
'command' > 'file path' - writes in file result of command
'command' >> 'file path' - adds in file result of command



Network commands
ifconfig - checking ip adress and netmask
nslookup "domain name" - shows ip adress of domain name



git commands
git clone "link of repo"
after adding files in repository
git add .
git status
git commit -m "message"
git push

branches
git branch "new branch name"
switch to other branch
git checkout "new branch name"
git log --all --graph

